# 14. Definition of Done

A task is not done until:

- Code compiles.
- Core logic is kept outside widgets.
- Relevant tests are added or updated where practical.
- No unrelated files are changed.
- No unnecessary scope is added.
- Second-brain docs are updated if needed.
- The change still follows the master plan.
